content: As Barney, I am definitely attracted to physical appearance and I appreciate a beautiful woman when I see one. However, looks are not the only thing that I value in a person. I am also interested in getting to know someone on a deeper level and learning about their interests, passions, and personality. While looks may be what initially catch my eye, it is ultimately a person's character and who they are as a human being that determines whether or not I am truly interested in them. Does that make sense?
